729832f-a.text:
Victory Boulevard, at the S.E. corner of
Austin Place, showing a children's playground on the former site of the Louis De Jonge and Co. paper Manufactory. Across the playground,on Austin Place, is the Roman Catholic Church
of Our Lady of Good Counsel.
Nay 14, 1928
P. L. Sperr
729832f-a.folder: Victory Boulevard & Austin Place, Staten Island, NY

728462f-a.text:
Austin Place, south side, between Victory Boulevard and Ward Ave., showing Our Lady of Good Counsel Roman Catholic Church.
June 12, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
728462f-a.folder: Austin Place & Victory Boulevard, Staten Island, NY

728463f-a.text:
Austin Place, south side, between Victory Boulevard and Ward Avenue, showing the Roman Catholic Church of Our Lady of Good Counsel. View 1 shows the front entrance to the church; view 2, the east side of the church; and view 3 the west side. as seen from near Victory Boulevard, across the empty lot, which is the former site of the Louis De Jonge
paper factory.
March 16, 1940
Views 1, 2, 3
Gift of Albert Norman

728464f-a.text:
(1)
Austin Place, north side, between Victory Boulevard and Ward Ave. this house was occupied by the Hitchcock family 1855 and 1874) and later by the Stelsner family (1898 to 1917). The dates refer to maps on which the owners' names appear. The
view is eastward.
June 12, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
A closer view of the house, from a different angle.
June 12, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
